#: ../../R/religion-of-CHI.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Case Western Reserve University] Yet another hackish parody religion (see "
"also :ref:`Church-of-the-SubGenius`\\, :ref:`Discordianism`\\). In the "
"mid-70s, the canonical \"Introduction to Programming\" courses at CWRU were "
"taught in Algol, and student exercises were punched on cards and run on a "
"Univac 1108 system using a homebrew operating system named CHI. The religion"
" had no doctrines and but one ritual: whenever the worshiper noted that a "
"digital clock read 11:08, he or she would recite the phrase \"It is 11:08; "
"ABS, ALPHABETIC, ARCSIN, ARCCOS, ARCTAN.\" The last five words were the "
"first five functions in the appropriate chapter of the Algol manual; note "
"the special pronunciations /obz/ and /ark´sin/ rather than the more common "
"/ahbz/ and /ark´si:n/. Using an alarm clock to warn of 11:08's arrival was "
":ref:`considered-harmful`\\."
msgstr ""
"[ケース・ウェスタン・リザーブ大学] またしてもハッカー的なパロディ宗教(\\ :ref:`Church-of-the-SubGenius`\\ 、\\"
" :ref:`Discordianism`\\ も参照)。70年代半ば、CWRUの定番「Introduction to "
"Programming」コースはAlgolで教えられ、学生の演習はカードにパンチされ、CHIという名の自家製OSを使ったUnivac "
"1108システムで実行された。この宗教には教義はなく、儀式が一つだけあった。信者はデジタル時計が11:08を示すのに気づくたびに、「It is "
"11:08; ABS, ALPHABETIC, ARCSIN, ARCCOS, "
"ARCTAN」という句を唱えるのである。最後の五つの単語は、Algolマニュアルの該当する章の最初の五つの関数だった。より一般的な/ahbz/や/ark´si:n/ではなく、特別な発音/obz/と/ark´sin/に注意せよ。11:08の到来を警告するために目覚まし時計を使うことは、\\"
" :ref:`considered-harmful`\\ とされた。"
